i need some comfort my cat had five kittens and this has been about or months ago i dont remember when but i grew so attached to them i forgot to mention that like a week after she had them another kitten found its way to the house the mother cat took it in like it was her own well now after i have grown so attached to them all five of her biological kittens have either been taken to different homes been ran over or my neighbors' stupid dog ate them one of them which was also my favorite disapeared today i am so hurt i am still glad that i have to one that wondered up here by itself but i am still greiveing over my other kittens can someone please give me some advice on how to cope i know this sounds stupid coming from an year old girl but i have always loved cats and kittens and this just hurts please help my heart goes out to you it is hard when you love animals and when you get attached all the harder i went through that when my husband's mom had kittens and i worked with them for two months to get them tame it worked and just as i had gotten one to come up on my lap the next door dog killed one and i saw it happen i ran and tried to stop it but it was to late i couldn't find the kitten anywhere later in the middle of the night we heard something at midnight that next morning there was the kitten at the door barely alive my husband put him in a basket and we raced to the vet to have it put down on the way there the kitten looked up at me and lifted it's paw and cried i knew it was asking for my help i cried so hard but there was nothing i could do that poor little thing must have crawled the whole night until it got to the door that is the noise we heard at midnight i couldn't even go to work that day i was so upset so you are not the only one that will grieve for a poor baby that dies it is normal and you should allow yourself to grieve look at it this way you must have a very tender and loving heart only a person like that would grieve for one of gods little creatures how sad for those that don't it is people like you with a loving heart that make our world a better place to live hugs Shaggy dog story Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Pitaten Ron and Fez Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Cat Phoebe Buffay's songs Garfield Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Time Out of Mind Ferret Atomic Kitten EastEnders John the Baptist AFI 100 Years series Piccolo Junior Saga W.I.T.C.H. Father's Day (Doctor Who) The Inside The Shining (film) Kitten The Marshall Mathers LP Socialization The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe The Jazz Singer StarCraft: Hybrid Doug Humphrey Bogart Marilyn Monroe She Loves You Fruits Basket RuneScape quests Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Joke The Star Wars Holiday Special The Lovely Bones Girly Blood on the Tracks One Tree Hill (TV series) Paul Is Dead Social rule Gia Carangi Grief The Amber Spyglass Grandview, U.S.A. Pok__mon Live! Looney Tunes and Merrie Melodies filmography Le Malade imaginaire 613 mitzvot Sin City What Ever Happened to Baby Jane? (film) Street-Legal Treehouse of Horror V Scenes from a Memory Frankie Laine Hall & Oates Year of the Spider Joy Division (band) Characters in the Smurfs Muslim ibn Aqeel Melanie Wilkes Minor characters in Teen Titans (animated series) Guinea pig El Goonish Shive Kimi Finster Dean Koontz Cindy Sheehan The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Fiddler on the Roof Toilet humour Billboard Hot 100 Virgin Mary in Islam Korban Cliff Richard Invader Zim One Life to Live StarCraft: Uprising Jade Emperor The Life and Times of Juniper Lee Kim Possible Xiaolin Showdown Pet skunk Fancy Crane Fred Phelps Sant Thakar Singh 2004 Republican National Convention Spanish verbs Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma 